    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-02-15T11:54:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-02-15T11:54:00-05:00" n="892"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d892">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">890F.515/5: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Saudi Arabia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Shullaw</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Jidda</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-02-15T20:00:00+03:06"
                            >February 15, 1943—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received February 17—12:53 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>16. My 12, February 10, 11 p.m. On February 13 a British warship brought 100,000
                    sovereigns to Jidda for the Saudi Government. This amount is equivalent to
                    roughly 5 million rials and is expected to tide Government over difficult
                    period. Wikeley believes further gold shipment must be requested in about 2
                    months.</p>
                <pb facs="0871" n="859" xml:id="pg_859"/>
                <p>Supply situation with India no longer able to export forces Saudi Government to
                    turn to Middle East Supply Corporation. Crops in the interior will be harvested
                    in 3 months and should help meet needs since rains have given hopes for good
                    yield.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Cairo.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Shullaw</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
